<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="233" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">
<bibRef pageId="4" pageNumber="233" refId="ref3638" type="journal article">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">
<title box="[199,290,367,392]" jopScore="1.1761006" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">Biology</title>
.
</emphasis>
Males and females of 
<emphasis box="[549,662,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">M. aureus</emphasis>
were obserVed flying near and resting on plants of 
<emphasis box="[1238,1397,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">Ornithogalum</emphasis>
sp. from the beginning of May to the beginning of June in 
<date box="[787,907,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="2011" valueMax="2013">
<year box="[787,843,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">2011</year>
-2013
</date>
and 
<pagination box="[965,1085,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" type="pagination">
<date box="[965,1085,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" value="2015" valueMax="2016">2015-2016</date>
</pagination>
(
<journalOrPublisher box="[1102,1218,404,429]" jopScore="1.5644498" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" type="_" typeScore="6">more than</journalOrPublisher>
<part box="[1227,1255,404,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="233" type="volume">50</part>
obserVations in total). Up to four adults were noted to sometimes rest simultaneously on the same plant leaVes. Females of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">M. aureus</emphasis>
were often obserVed settling for oViposition between the base of an 
<emphasis box="[1063,1222,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="233">Ornithogalum</emphasis>
sp. plant and the surrounding soil, behaVing as if they were laying eggs on the ground, Very close to the plant. HoweVer, we neVer found eggs. The females made intermittent buzzing sounds while maintaining their positions for oVer fiVe minutes. Thereafter, they cleaned themselVes for a few minutes before flying away.
</bibRef>
</paragraph>
